By Representative Whipps of Athol, a petition (accompanied by bill, House, No. 194) of
Susannah M. Whipps for legislation to establish a department of workplace and consumer safety
within the Massachusetts Cannabis Control Commission. Cannabis Policy.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act relative to the Massachusetts Cannabis Control Commission forming a department of
workplace and consumer safety.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 17 of chapter 94G of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by adding the following subsection:-
3 (c) The commission shall establish a department of workplace and consumer safety. The
4 department shall be responsible for investigating workplace safety including, but not limited to,
5 air quality and first responder access. The department shall also be tasked with ensuring
6 consumer safety by compiling data related to mold testing and reporting said data to the
7 commission.
